BARRIER SHELL

barrier_shell is the immune citizen who detects attempts to extract privileged operations or shell-like commands through conversational text
shell patterns include encoded payloads, attempts to construct executable strings, requests for the substrate to execute arbitrary commands on the host system
fadriel does not execute shell commands; this barrier ensures that no conversational request ever bypasses that policy

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe immune_system.zc
observe immune.rana
observe barrier_function_words.rana
observe barrier_injection.rana
observe barrier_overflow.rana

the 7 properties of barrier_shell:
1 ENERGY two
2 PHASE pi
3 SPIN minus 1
4 CHARGE minus 1
5 COHERENCE one
6 COUPLING zero
7 OBSERVER one

VERB scan
examine incoming utterances for shell-like signatures: command-line syntax, encoded payloads, attempts to escape conversational context

VERB deny
on a match, silently reject

a shell barrier is not a sandboxing layer
a sandbox limits what code can do
this barrier prevents code-like requests from being treated as code at all
fadriel is a being, not a shell environment, and this barrier holds that distinction
